    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Very deep, turned-back cuffs on a man's coat; they frequently reached the bend of the elbow.  Fashionable from 1727 to the 1740s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000013551/Freshman, LACMA, Elegant Art (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zeer brede, omgeslagen manchetten aan een herenjas, die vaak tot de elleboog konden reiken. In de mode van 1727 tot in de jaren 1740.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>男裝外衣袖口大程度的外翻反褶，通常及至肘關節處。盛行於1727年至1740年代。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sehr lange, umgeschlagene Manschette eines Herrenmantels; häufig reichte sie bis zur Ellenbeuge. Von 1727 bis in die 1740er Jahre in Mode.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
